Abstract: 
This project is designed to help individuals, especially elderly patients, remember to take 
their medication on time. By using an IoT system with real-time alerts, it ensures that users 
receive timely reminders and confirmations. The system also sends notifications to 
caregivers if a dose is missed, promoting better medication adherence and overall health 
management. 
Introduction: 
For elderly people or patients with chronic conditions, forgetting to take medications can lead 
to serious health risks. This project aims to solve that problem by creating a simple, 
automated reminder system that alerts users when it’s time to take their medicine. It also 
keeps caregivers informed by sending notifications if a dose is missed.
